===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[monitor]]''', '''[[warner]]''', from perfect passive participle '''[[monitus]]''', ''warning'', from verb '''[[monere]]''', ''warn'' or ''threaten''

==English==
===Noun===
'''monitor''', plural '''monitors'''

# someone who watches over something.
# person in charge of something or someone.
# device similar to a [[television set]] used as to give a graphical display of the output from a [[computer]].
# class of warship designed for shore bombardment rather than combat with other ships.

